# CODEOWNERS — defines who must review changes to sensitive areas of the codebase.
# GitHub automatically requests a review from the listed owner(s) when a PR
# touches a matching path. Combined with `require_code_owner_review: true` in
# `.github/rulesets/org-main-protection.json`, no PR can be merged without approval
# from the domain team for that area.
#
# Syntax: <pattern>  <owner> [<owner2> ...]
# Owners are GitHub org team slugs (@smetalab/team-slug).
# More specific patterns override less specific ones listed above them.
# Teams must exist in the smetalab GitHub Organization before these rules apply.
# Run scripts/create-org-teams.sh to create all required teams.
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ── Infrastructure layer (auth, email, notifications, payments) ──────────────
/lib/infrastructure/  @smetalab/platform

# ── Authentication ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Security-critical path — requires explicit security team approval on every change.
/lib/infrastructure/auth/  @smetalab/security

# ── Payments / billing ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/lib/infrastructure/payments/  @smetalab/payments

# ── Database schema ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Schema changes are irreversible without a migration.
/lib/data/db/schema.ts  @smetalab/platform

# ── Drizzle migrations and config ────────────────────────────────────────────
/drizzle/  @smetalab/platform
/drizzle.config.mts  @smetalab/platform
/drizzle.config.test.mts  @smetalab/platform

# ── Server actions ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/app/actions/  @smetalab/platform

# ── GitHub configuration (CI, branch protection, CODEOWNERS) ─────────────────
/.github/  @smetalab/admins
/.github/rulesets/  @smetalab/admins
/.github/workflows/  @smetalab/admins
